    <h5>When should I get professional help for my child?</h5>
    <p>Sometimes, despite being safe with calm, supportive, trusted adults and having a chance to readjust over a few weeks, a child's anxiety symptoms may not diminish, or they may be so intense that they interfere with his or her home life, school work, or activities with friends. This is a time to get professional help. Parents should trust their intuition and get help even if their child doesn't meet all these criteria. Consider seeking help from a doctor or counselor when:</p>
